# Mission Accepted — Project Overview

A single-page interactive **invitation landing experience** ("Thursday's Main Character Invitation") built with TanStack Start + React 19, deployed to Cloudflare Workers.

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Tool / Version |
|---|---|
| Language | TypeScript 5.8 |
| UI | React 19 |
| Framework | TanStack Start ^1.167 (SSR, file-based routing) |
| Router | TanStack Router ^1.168 |
| Build | Vite 7 |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 (`@import "tailwindcss"` in `src/styles.css`) |
| Animation | Framer Motion 12 |
| FX | canvas-confetti |
| Icons | lucide-react |
| UI Primitives | Radix UI (shadcn-style, under `src/components/ui/`) |
| Deploy target | **Cloudflare Workers** via `wrangler.jsonc` |
| Package manager | **Bun** (`bun.lock` present — use `bun install`, `bun run dev`, etc.) |

---

## Project Structure

```
src/
  routes/
    __root.tsx      # HTML shell, QueryClientProvider, global <head> meta
    index.tsx       # The entire invitation page (only route: "/")
  components/ui/   # ~45 shadcn-style Radix components (available but mostly unused by index.tsx)
  hooks/
    use-mobile.tsx  # Mobile breakpoint helper
  lib/
    utils.ts        # cn() helper (clsx + tailwind-merge)
    error-page.ts   # SSR error HTML renderer
    error-capture.ts # Cloudflare Worker error capture
  styles.css        # Tailwind v4 entry, CSS custom properties, @keyframes
  router.tsx        # createRouter() wiring routeTree + QueryClient
  start.ts          # createStart() with error-catching server middleware
  server.ts         # Cloudflare Worker fetch export wrapping TanStack Start SSR
  routeTree.gen.ts  # Auto-generated by TanStack Router — DO NOT edit manually

vite.config.ts      # Standard Vite config (tanstackStart + tailwind + tsConfigPaths + cloudflare)
wrangler.jsonc      # Cloudflare Worker config — main: src/server.ts
components.json     # shadcn/ui config (style: new-york, alias: @/)
tsconfig.json       # Path alias: @/* → ./src/*
```

---

## Routing

- **File-based routing** — TanStack Router scans `src/routes/`
- Only one route exists: **`/`** (`src/routes/index.tsx`)
- `routeTree.gen.ts` is auto-generated — never edit it by hand; run `bun run dev` or `bun run build` to regenerate
- Root layout is in `src/routes/__root.tsx`

---

## The Main Page (`src/routes/index.tsx`)

The entire invitation UX lives here. Key features:
- Animated hero with rotating subtitle list
- RSVP buttons with confetti burst (`canvas-confetti`)
- "Wrong button" that dodges/shakes (evasion gag)
- "Mission Brief" card grid with icons
- Live countdown to next Thursday 7 PM
- Floating background particles, gradient blobs, cursor glow
- Google Fonts loaded client-side: Plus Jakarta Sans, Fraunces, JetBrains Mono

This file is large (~524 lines). All logic is self-contained — no external state management, no API calls.

---

## Styling Rules

- Tailwind v4 is used — **no `tailwind.config.js`** (config is in `src/styles.css` via `@theme`)
- CSS custom properties are defined in `src/styles.css`: `--pink`, `--gold`, `--cream`, `--ink`, `--bg`, etc.
- Class utility: always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` when combining conditional classes
- Animation keyframes (`float-up`, `pulse-glow`, etc.) are declared in `src/styles.css`

---

## Component Conventions

- Use **functional components** only — no class components
- Prefer **inline Tailwind** for one-off styles; extract to a component only when reused 3+ times
- All shadcn/ui components live in `src/components/ui/` — add new ones with the shadcn CLI: `bunx shadcn@latest add <name>`
- Path alias `@/` maps to `src/` — always use it for imports

---

## SSR & Cloudflare

- `src/server.ts` is the Cloudflare Worker entry (`export default { fetch }`)
- `src/start.ts` sets up TanStack Start with server-side error middleware
- For local dev: `bun run dev` (uses Cloudflare's local Worker runtime via `@cloudflare/vite-plugin`)
- For production: `bun run build` then deploy via Wrangler (`bunx wrangler deploy`)
- Secrets go in `.dev.vars` (gitignored) for local, and Wrangler secrets for production

---

## Environment / Config

- **No `.env` files committed** — `.dev.vars` is the local secrets file (gitignored)
- `VITE_*` env vars are available in client code via `import.meta.env.VITE_*`
- No external APIs or database calls in the current codebase

---

## Commands

```bash
bun install          # Install dependencies
bun run dev          # Start local dev server (Cloudflare Worker runtime)
bun run build        # Production build
bun run preview      # Preview production build locally
bun run lint         # ESLint check
bun run format       # Prettier format
```

---

## Key Constraints

- **Do not add** any `lovable`, `lovable-tagger`, or `@lovable.dev/*` references — this project was migrated away from Lovable
- **Do not edit** `src/routeTree.gen.ts` — it is auto-generated
- Tailwind v4 does NOT use `tailwind.config.js` — put theme tokens in `src/styles.css` `@theme` block
- `@cloudflare/vite-plugin` and `@tanstack/react-start` both handle SSR — do not add conflicting SSR plugins
- React is deduplicated via `resolve.dedupe` in `vite.config.ts` — do not add duplicate React packages
